### ============================================================
### Incident Platform Example
### ============================================================
### Expected JWT claims for the tokens below:
### - admin token:   role=admin, tenant_id=aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa
### - member token:  role=member, tenant_id=aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa
### ============================================================

@base = http://localhost:3300/v1
@admin_token = Bearer <admin-jwt-token>
@member_token = Bearer <member-jwt-token>
@org_id = aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa
@user_id = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
@service_id = 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111
@ingest_key = incident-platform-ingest-key

### ============================================================
### 0. Development helpers
### ============================================================

### Mint an admin JWT for local testing
GET http://localhost:3300/dev/token?user_id={{user_id}}&role=admin&tenant_id={{org_id}}

### Mint a member JWT for local testing
GET http://localhost:3300/dev/token?user_id={{user_id}}&role=member&tenant_id={{org_id}}

### Inspect locally received outbound webhook deliveries
GET http://localhost:3300/dev/webhook-sink

### ============================================================
### 1. Services
### ============================================================

### Create a service
POST {{base}}/services
Authorization: {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Worker API",
  "slug": "worker-api",
  "tier": "high",
  "status": "healthy",
  "owner_team": "Platform",
  "runbook_url": "https://runbooks.example.com/worker-api",
  "created_by": "{{user_id}}"
}

### List services
GET {{base}}/services?filter[status]=healthy
Authorization: {{member_token}}

### ============================================================
### 2. Incidents
### ============================================================

### Create an incident
### room_key is required by current validation, but the controller rewrites it
### from the slug to incident:<slug>.
POST {{base}}/incidents
Authorization: {{member_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "service_id": "{{service_id}}",
  "title": "Payments API latency spike",
  "slug": "payments-api-latency-spike",
  "severity": "sev2",
  "summary": "p95 latency exceeded the on-call threshold for 12 minutes.",
  "commander_id": "{{user_id}}",
  "room_key": "temporary-room",
  "created_by": "{{user_id}}"
}

### Acknowledge an incident
PATCH {{base}}/incidents/<incident-id>
Authorization: {{member_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "acknowledged",
  "commander_id": "{{user_id}}"
}

### Resolve an incident
PATCH {{base}}/incidents/<incident-id>
Authorization: {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-Resolution-Reason: Error budget burn stopped after rollback

{
  "status": "resolved",
  "summary": "Rollback completed and latency returned to baseline."
}

### ============================================================
### 3. Alerts
### ============================================================

### Ingest an alert with API key auth
### Current limitation: API keys are not tenant-bound, so org_id is explicit.
POST {{base}}/alerts
X-API-Key: {{ingest_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "org_id": "{{org_id}}",
  "service_id": "{{service_id}}",
  "external_id": "pd-evt-0001",
  "source": "pagerduty",
  "severity": "sev2",
  "fingerprint": "payments-api-latency-p95",
  "summary": "PagerDuty detected sustained latency in Payments API.",
  "payload": {
    "source": "pagerduty",
    "dedupe_key": "payments-api-latency-p95",
    "triggered_at": "2026-03-17T12:00:00Z"
  }
}

### List alerts
GET {{base}}/alerts?filter[source]=pagerduty
Authorization: {{member_token}}

### Link an alert to an incident manually
PATCH {{base}}/alerts/<alert-id>
Authorization: {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "incident_id": "<incident-id>",
  "status": "linked"
}

### ============================================================
### 4. Attachments
### ============================================================

### Upload an attachment
### Multipart uploads currently require org_id and created_by explicitly.
POST {{base}}/attachments
Authorization: {{member_token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=ShaperailBoundary

--ShaperailBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="org_id"

{{org_id}}
--ShaperailBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="incident_id"

<incident-id>
--ShaperailBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="kind"

log
--ShaperailBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="created_by"

{{user_id}}
--ShaperailBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file_url"; filename="incident-log.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

replace-this-section-with-log-contents
--ShaperailBoundary--

### ============================================================
### 5. GraphQL
### ============================================================

POST http://localhost:3300/graphql
Authorization: {{member_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "query IncidentBoard { list_incidents(limit: 20, offset: 0) { id title severity status room_key service { id name status } } }"
}

### ============================================================
### 6. Inbound webhook route
### ============================================================

### The signature header must match PAGERDUTY_WEBHOOK_SECRET.
POST http://localhost:3300/webhooks/pagerduty
X-Shaperail-Signature: sha256=<replace-with-valid-signature>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "incident.triggered",
  "service_id": "{{service_id}}",
  "title": "Payments API paging event",
  "payload": {
    "provider": "pagerduty"
  }
}
